WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:31.209 --> 00:02:32.543
What are they doing?

3
00:02:33.086 --> 00:02:36.297
It's a game.

4
00:02:36.672 --> 00:02:40.130
They stand with a big stick.

5
00:02:40.134 --> 00:02:42.049
see how to lay the long cord.

6
00:02:42.053 --> 00:02:45.390
and where to stand
the little sticks.

7
00:02:47.225 --> 00:02:49.852
Why do they do it here?

8
00:38:13.599 --> 00:38:17.682
If my father came down
from the mountains.

9
00:38:17.686 --> 00:38:20.602
he would see how it is.

10
00:38:20.606 --> 00:38:24.898
The deer and elk stay
wide of the valley now.

11
00:38:24.902 --> 00:38:27.530
To hunt them.

12
00:38:27.655 --> 00:38:30.195
we must follow west
where K'uu-ch'ish hunts.

13
00:38:30.199 --> 00:38:33.657
or east where there are Pima.

14
00:38:33.661 --> 00:38:36.284
And fight our neighbors

15
00:38:36.288 --> 00:38:38.119
in places sacred to them.

16
00:38:38.123 --> 00:38:42.211
All for fear of a few
tents at the river.

17
00:38:44.463 --> 00:38:45.381
Pionsenay...

18
00:38:46.215 --> 00:38:48.801
what did you hunt?

19
00:38:49.760 --> 00:38:51.220
We can't eat that.

20
00:38:52.680 --> 00:38:55.391
I shouldn't see the Mimbreños
of the plains where I go.

21
00:38:56.350 --> 00:38:57.560
but now I have.

22
00:38:58.644 --> 00:38:59.895
I saw one of these men

23
00:39:00.563 --> 00:39:02.481
hunted and killed
for taking a deer.

24
00:39:03.482 --> 00:39:05.772
from where he shouldn't be.

25
00:39:05.776 --> 00:39:07.861
We saw him killed.

26
00:39:09.363 --> 00:39:11.490
beneath us. over a deer.

27
00:39:12.324 --> 00:39:16.078
My family is well provided
for in the high places.

28
00:39:17.037 --> 00:39:18.330
We aren't hungry.

29
00:39:19.456 --> 00:39:22.998
We don't live in fear.

30
00:39:23.002 --> 00:39:27.586
Pionsenay grew impatient watching
the white-eyes on the plains.

31
00:39:27.590 --> 00:39:31.051
Now he has brought
them into my home.

32
00:39:32.720 --> 00:39:33.721
Do you see this?

33
00:39:34.346 --> 00:39:35.302
This is what I brought.

34
00:39:35.306 --> 00:39:37.474
They are no more danger to you

35
00:39:38.058 --> 00:39:39.518
than the ones

36
00:39:40.060 --> 00:39:42.855
who lost them. at the river.

37
00:39:43.606 --> 00:39:47.981
The men are gone. I see that.

38
00:39:47.985 --> 00:39:51.484
But where they've been.
their sons will follow.

39
00:39:51.488 --> 00:39:53.949
And when they are able.

40
00:39:54.867 --> 00:39:57.036
the sons will hunt after you.

41
00:39:57.661 --> 00:40:00.456
And they will hunt
after all the People.

42
00:40:01.123 --> 00:40:05.457
not knowing which of us you are.

43
00:40:05.461 --> 00:40:10.170
It will be the same for
them. as well as their sons.

44
00:40:10.174 --> 00:40:12.756
But they will not find me asleep

45
00:40:12.760 --> 00:40:15.550
in the mountains like my father.

46
00:40:15.554 --> 00:40:17.886
who was once a great war-chief.

47
00:40:17.890 --> 00:40:20.221
but who has grown old.

48
00:40:20.225 --> 00:40:22.895
Then you will leave here.

49
00:40:23.520 --> 00:40:26.899
Yes. I leave this place

50
00:40:27.483 --> 00:40:28.897
where the People

51
00:40:28.901 --> 00:40:31.987
are too frightened
to sing for me.

52
00:40:32.488 --> 00:40:35.783
This. too. was in my dream.

53
00:40:36.533 --> 00:40:39.495
You will go and wait for
the white-eyes on the plain

54
00:40:40.204 --> 00:40:41.455
and you will not sleep.

55
00:40:42.122 --> 00:40:45.542
You who've made these
people your enemy.

56
00:40:46.251 --> 00:40:49.380
You will fight them for
as long as you are able.

57
00:40:50.005 --> 00:40:51.670
and still they will come.

58
00:40:51.674 --> 00:40:54.172
And when you wish to hide

59
00:40:54.176 --> 00:40:56.720
the high places will
no longer hide you.

60
00:40:57.846 --> 00:41:01.012
Then you'll see the
white-eyes I see.

61
00:41:01.016 --> 00:41:04.353
And you will know

62
00:41:05.646 --> 00:41:10.734
why I don't sing for
your victory today.

63
00:41:13.529 --> 00:41:15.989
Now they can choose.

64
00:41:17.116 --> 00:41:19.368
who are free to go as they will.

65
00:41:19.910 --> 00:41:26.625
I have no more to tell them.

66
00:41:30.504 --> 00:41:31.630
I take this.

67
00:41:34.091 --> 00:41:37.594
so it won't disturb the
sleep of an old man.

68
00:43:07.351 --> 00:43:08.352
Follow it out some.

69
00:43:09.520 --> 00:43:11.939
See if they stay grouped.
or if any cut back.

70
00:47:51.009 --> 00:47:53.512
My sister is not
the same person.

71
00:47:54.888 --> 00:47:57.099
She doesn't have the
man for her home.

72
00:47:58.600 --> 00:48:00.894
whom she loved
before she was born.

73
00:48:02.312 --> 00:48:04.727
There's no more father
for her daughters.

74
00:48:04.731 --> 00:48:07.442
They'll have a father.

75
00:48:08.485 --> 00:48:10.487
They'll come with us.

76
00:48:11.071 --> 00:48:13.240
Why would anyone
want to go with you?

77
00:48:20.247 --> 00:48:22.290
Will the white-eyes
from the river

78
00:48:23.250 --> 00:48:25.039
come to us. now?

79
00:48:25.043 --> 00:48:26.128
No

80
00:48:26.795 --> 00:48:30.128
The people are safe here.

81
00:48:30.132 --> 00:48:34.298
But more white-eyes
will come to the river.

82
00:48:34.302 --> 00:48:35.804
That is the old man's dream.

83
00:48:36.930 --> 00:48:39.015
What is your dream. Taklishim?

84
00:48:41.726 --> 00:48:43.687
I don't dream about this.

85
00:48:44.479 --> 00:48:47.607
They have come and put
their sticks in our way.

86
00:48:48.191 --> 00:48:49.897
and it's our bad luck

87
00:48:49.901 --> 00:48:50.902
they've done this.

88
00:48:52.988 --> 00:48:54.614
That's all I know.

89
00:48:55.240 --> 00:48:56.658
It's bad luck.

90
00:52:19.652 --> 00:52:22.655
If he goes. I go with him.

91
00:52:27.994 --> 00:52:28.828
Come here.

92
00:52:33.917 --> 00:52:36.127
You listened to what was said.

93
00:52:38.588 --> 00:52:39.756
Did you understand?

94
00:52:46.388 --> 00:52:47.472
Good.

95
00:52:49.516 --> 00:52:51.810
I'm glad my son

96
00:52:53.895 --> 00:52:57.273
knows who he is.

97
00:53:06.199 --> 00:53:07.659
It has told me

98
00:53:08.451 --> 00:53:10.241
where ponies of mine were

99
00:53:10.245 --> 00:53:11.621
that were stolen.

100
00:53:12.455 --> 00:53:13.540
You can speak to it

101
00:53:14.749 --> 00:53:19.421
when there's trouble.

102
00:53:23.007 --> 00:53:27.595
I think... I will see you again.

103
00:53:57.375 --> 00:53:59.210
And what is there for you?

104
00:54:11.764 --> 00:54:15.477
I don't need the
gift my brother has.

105
00:54:15.977 --> 00:54:18.938
You give me enough.

106
00:58:07.041 --> 00:58:08.751
I don't follow Pionsenay.

107
00:58:12.505 --> 00:58:13.798
I'll follow you.

108
02:15:48.823 --> 02:15:49.741
You're all right.

109
02:15:50.450 --> 02:15:51.493
Stay still.

110
02:15:51.993 --> 02:15:53.078
This is a game.

111
02:16:13.515 --> 02:16:15.225
Go outside.

112
02:16:21.773 --> 02:16:23.400
Don't move.

113
02:16:24.109 --> 02:16:25.276
They're almost done.

114
02:40:43.650 --> 02:40:45.439
What are you doing?

115
02:40:45.443 --> 02:40:47.320
You're too far.

116
02:40:55.620 --> 02:40:56.705
Tarak!

117
02:40:57.289 --> 02:40:58.582
You're too far.

118
02:41:07.924 --> 02:41:10.385
You're too far. Tarak!

119
02:41:40.624 --> 02:41:43.043
You're too far. Tarak.

120
